but how are the rest of the team?

258
00:18:29.401 --> 00:18:31.462
They're great.

259
00:18:31.486 --> 00:18:33.923
You know. incredibly smart. driven.

260
00:18:33.947 --> 00:18:34.948
Best of the best.

261
00:18:36.283 --> 00:18:37.594
And they all hate my guts.

262
00:18:37.618 --> 00:18:39.846
Come on. That can't be true.

263
00:18:39.870 --> 00:18:42.599
It's Walt's crew. and I'm the outsider.

264
00:18:42.623 --> 00:18:45.435
Well. it's not the worst thing for
people at work not to love you.

265
00:18:45.459 --> 00:18:46.460
They bother you less.

266
00:18:47.753 --> 00:18:49.421
You would say that.

267
00:18:50.506 --> 00:18:53.592
No. I just… I want them
to know I'm a team player.

268
00:18:55.260 --> 00:18:57.030
Well. I'm glad to hear you say that.

269
00:18:57.054 --> 00:18:58.764
You know. I wasn't
sure if after your dad…

270
00:19:01.141 --> 00:19:03.828
If you'd still be up for it.
or if you'd need more time.

271
00:19:03.852 --> 00:19:05.395
Which would be totally understandable.

272
00:19:07.272 --> 00:19:08.273
No. it's…

273
00:19:09.066 --> 00:19:10.234
It's the opposite.

274
00:19:12.152 --> 00:19:14.112
This mission meant so much to him.

275
00:19:14.988 --> 00:19:17.050
and he was actually the one
who pushed me to get on the crew

276
00:19:17.074 --> 00:19:18.408
as a pilot in the first place.

277
00:19:19.868 --> 00:19:21.828
I really was sorry to hear about him.

278
00:19:24.581 --> 00:19:27.417
It's been over a month…

279
00:19:29.586 --> 00:19:31.588
And it still feels like it
happened yesterday.

280
00:19:35.300 --> 00:19:38.428
Sometimes I come home
from work and I still expect to

281
00:19:39.012 --> 00:19:41.074
hear him bitching about
that damn ankle monitor.

282
00:19:41.098 --> 00:19:42.432
Yeah.

283
00:19:42.933 --> 00:19:46.371
Those things that drive
you crazy about them.

284
00:19:46.395 --> 00:19:48.146
those are the things you miss the most.

285
00:19:49.189 --> 00:19:50.250
Yeah.

286
00:19:50.274 --> 00:19:51.400
Starting to see that.

287
00:19:52.776 --> 00:19:56.589
But it's made me appreciate
the time I have with my kids now.

288
00:19:56.613 --> 00:19:59.074
Even though I still mostly
just complain about them.

289
00:20:00.117 --> 00:20:01.201
How are they?

290
00:20:01.910 --> 00:20:03.888
Javi's been touring with his band.

291
00:20:03.912 --> 00:20:05.706
My god.

292
00:20:06.290 --> 00:20:08.393
I would love to hear some
of his music sometime.

293
00:20:08.417 --> 00:20:10.502
No. you wouldn't.

294
00:20:12.296 --> 00:20:14.131
And graciana…

295
00:20:14.715 --> 00:20:17.515
She couldn't wait for me to leave.
Practically booted me out the door.

296
00:20:18.886 --> 00:20:20.029
Same with Alex.

297
00:20:20.053 --> 00:20:21.972
He can't wait to get
the whole hab to himself.

298
00:20:23.599 --> 00:20:26.935
Okay. one last shot and
then we're going to bed.

299
00:20:28.729 --> 00:20:30.480
- Right?
- Yeah.

300
00:20:51.043 --> 00:20:52.044
Aunt aleida.

301
00:20:54.171 --> 00:20:56.924
Aunt aleida. wake up.

302
00:20:58.050 --> 00:21:00.469
Fucking hell.

303
00:21:05.390 --> 00:21:06.391
Alex?

304
00:21:08.393 --> 00:21:10.687
Wow.

305
00:21:12.481 --> 00:21:13.565
You got huge.

306
00:21:14.775 --> 00:21:15.817
Mars gravity.

307
00:21:16.777 --> 00:21:17.778
Is that coffee?

308
00:21:18.487 --> 00:21:19.756
Yes. Yes.

309
00:21:19.780 --> 00:21:21.281
And aspirin.

310
00:21:25.202 --> 00:21:26.453
She raised you well.

311
00:21:27.871 --> 00:21:30.707
Speaking of which. where is your mom?

312
00:21:32.584 --> 00:21:33.645
Not sure.

313
00:21:33.669 --> 00:21:36.439
But she was in rough
shape this morning too.

314
00:21:36.463 --> 00:21:38.107
What the hell did you
two get up to last night?

315
00:21:38.131 --> 00:21:39.258
You know.

316
00:21:39.925 --> 00:21:41.260
Just catching up.

317
00:21:42.386 --> 00:21:45.389
Hey. you're going to helios. right?

318
00:21:46.223 --> 00:21:47.784
Yeah. Yes. yes.

319
00:21:47.808 --> 00:21:49.351
All right.

320
00:21:50.018 --> 00:21:51.079
I'll come with you.

321
00:21:51.103 --> 00:21:52.354
Give me five minutes.

322
00:21:52.896 --> 00:21:55.649
Just need a second.

323
00:21:58.402 --> 00:22:00.380
You know. I… no. no.

324
00:22:00.404 --> 00:22:01.405
No. no.

325
00:22:02.614 --> 00:22:03.782
Give me ten minutes.

326
00:22:06.910 --> 00:22:07.995
Okay. cool.

327
00:22:56.877 --> 00:22:58.980
There you are. How was the ride?

328
00:22:59.004 --> 00:23:00.506
Did you talk to opef about me?

329
00:23:01.089 --> 00:23:02.358
Well. hello to you too.

330
00:23:02.382 --> 00:23:03.383
Come on in.

331
00:23:04.676 --> 00:23:05.928
What'd you say to them?

332
00:23:07.012 --> 00:23:11.600
Well. I told them that
you are incredibly bright.

333
00:23:12.434 --> 00:23:16.688
Highly motivated. tenacious. and
that they'd be lucky to have you.

334
00:23:17.189 --> 00:23:18.190
What else?

335
00:23:19.650 --> 00:23:21.068
They asked about your family.

336
00:23:21.568 --> 00:23:22.629
My dad?

337
00:23:22.653 --> 00:23:25.965
And your uncle. And your
grand mama. and your grandaddy too.

338
00:23:25.989 --> 00:23:26.990
What'd you say?

339
00:23:27.991 --> 00:23:30.911
I said that your father was very talented.

340
00:23:31.912 --> 00:23:35.183
But that he had serious
psychological issues.

341
00:23:35.207 --> 00:23:37.287
They already know that.
It's in his service records.

342
00:23:39.044 --> 00:23:40.170
I said that

343
00:23:40.879 --> 00:23:42.840
living in the shadow of what he did…

344
00:23:44.466 --> 00:23:45.759
It wasn't easy on you.

345
00:23:46.593 --> 00:23:49.721
It was a burden you took up.
and it wasn't yours to carry.

346
00:23:53.809 --> 00:23:55.269
They're giving me a second poly.

347
00:23:55.769 --> 00:23:56.770
Good.

348
00:23:57.938 --> 00:23:59.123
Good.

349
00:23:59.147 --> 00:24:00.917
That means you're still in the running.

350
00:24:00.941 --> 00:24:03.670
In fact. it means they really like you.

351
00:24:03.694 --> 00:24:06.280
Otherwise. they wouldn't
bother giving you a second shot.

352
00:24:12.911 --> 00:24:13.912
I just…

353
00:24:14.496 --> 00:24:15.890
I can't screw it up.

354
00:24:15.914 --> 00:24:17.875
- Then be honest.
- I was.

355
00:24:18.542 --> 00:24:19.710
My dad. he's not…

356
00:24:20.544 --> 00:24:22.105
He's never been part of my life.

357
00:24:22.129 --> 00:24:23.547
I don't give a shit about him.

358
00:24:27.926 --> 00:24:29.511
Avery. come sit down.

359
00:24:34.224 --> 00:24:35.225
Your dad

360
00:24:35.726 --> 00:24:37.728
became an astronaut because

361
00:24:39.605 --> 00:24:41.773
he had something to prove to the world.

362
00:24:42.524 --> 00:24:45.903
That he could live up to
the legacy of his parents.

363
00:24:46.737 --> 00:24:49.615
And because he thought that
that was what was expected of him.

364
00:24:51.283 --> 00:24:52.701
But deep in his heart.

365
00:24:53.368 --> 00:24:54.578
it wasn't what he wanted.

366
00:24:55.621 --> 00:24:56.622
He lied

367
00:24:57.331 --> 00:25:02.211
to his superiors. to ed.
to me. and to himself.

368
00:25:03.879 --> 00:25:05.631
That is what killed him.

369
00:25:06.840 --> 00:25:09.593
And if you're doing all this
just to prove you aren't him.

370
00:25:10.219 --> 00:25:11.779
you'll fail too.

371
00:25:11.803 --> 00:25:13.490
I want my own life.

372
00:25:13.514 --> 00:25:14.574
No one else's.

373
00:25:14.598 --> 00:25:16.058
Then tell them that.

374
00:25:16.558 --> 00:25:18.519
That is what they need to hear.

375
00:25:21.772 --> 00:25:23.249
Excuse me.

376
00:25:23.273 --> 00:25:25.835
You gonna just walk on through
here and not say hello to Avery?

377
00:25:25.859 --> 00:25:27.236
Hi. Avery!

378
00:25:29.112 --> 00:25:31.114
- She's getting big.
- Too big.

379
00:25:31.740 --> 00:25:32.940
I can hardly keep up with her.

380
00:25:35.077 --> 00:25:37.138
Come on. eat something.

381
00:25:37.162 --> 00:25:39.540
Actually. I should get back to Pendleton.

382
00:25:40.040 --> 00:25:42.727
Already? Wait. you just got here.

383
00:25:42.751 --> 00:25:43.919
Yeah.

384
00:25:44.711 --> 00:25:46.272
I'm sorry I came in so hot.

385
00:25:46.296 --> 00:25:47.506
Come here.

386
00:25:49.508 --> 00:25:51.426
You know I love you
no matter what. right?

387
00:25:52.052 --> 00:25:55.222
And you're gonna need that fire
in your belly for what's to come.

388
00:25:56.431 --> 00:25:57.516
I love you too.

389
00:26:03.689 --> 00:26:04.898
I'm surprised to see that.

390
00:26:05.482 --> 00:26:07.734
After everything that
happened between you.

391
00:26:10.195 --> 00:26:11.780
Love. hate.

392
00:26:12.447 --> 00:26:17.035
The older you get. the more you
start to realize they're not so different.

393
00:26:22.666 --> 00:26:27.272
The war of words between corporate
rivals in the space race is heating up

394
00:26:27.296 --> 00:26:31.317
as dueling missions to titan are
launching within days of each other.

395
00:26:31.341 --> 00:26:35.071
Russian aerospace firm kuragin
launched their craft. kosmos-1.

396
00:26:35.095 --> 00:26:36.698
from Kazakhstan just yesterday.

397
00:26:36.722 --> 00:26:38.283
While the helios-funded mission

398
00:26:38.307 --> 00:26:41.327
is said to launch from
Mars in less than a week.

399
00:26:41.351 --> 00:26:45.206
They both seek to be the first to
find signs of life in our solar system.

400
00:26:45.230 --> 00:26:48.710
Protests have grown in
regions of the Soviet union.

401
00:26:48.734 --> 00:26:51.087
the largest in Vilnius and Kiev.

402
00:26:51.111 --> 00:26:53.715
as members of anti-Soviet
independence movements

403
00:26:53.739 --> 00:26:57.343
are spreading in the wake
of the flailing Soviet economy.

404
00:26:57.367 --> 00:26:59.971
Along with the us and other m-6 nations.

405
00:26:59.995 --> 00:27:03.850
Moscow has invested heavily
in iridium mining on Mars.

406
00:27:03.874 --> 00:27:05.643
But shipments of the valuable resource

407
00:27:05.667 --> 00:27:09.671
have slowed as tensions at
happy valley continue to rise.

408
00:27:11.131 --> 00:27:14.819
You were appointed to your
post with very clear instructions.

409
00:27:14.843 --> 00:27:19.515
To implement our plans to expedite
shipments of iridium. no matter the cost.

410
00:27:20.057 --> 00:27:23.977
And these past weeks. the
work has slowed to a crawl.

411
00:27:24.645 --> 00:27:27.081
You know I am fond of you. my boy

412
00:27:27.105 --> 00:27:31.711
but we have leveraged our
entire economy on getting iridium

413
00:27:31.735 --> 00:27:34.047
and the people are
growing tired of waiting.

414
00:27:34.071 --> 00:27:38.450
You must expedite the next
phase of the kuragin project.

415
00:27:39.034 --> 00:27:42.579
I know you can rise to the
occasion. lenya. Goodbye.

416
00:27:49.545 --> 00:27:51.839
He is angry…

417
00:27:53.549 --> 00:27:54.549
Of course he is.

418
00:27:56.093 --> 00:27:59.054
What are you going
to do about this mess?

419
00:28:01.974 --> 00:28:05.018
I need to find a way to turn the page.

420
00:28:06.520 --> 00:28:09.999
Get people focused again on their work.

421
00:28:10.023 --> 00:28:13.419
They're still bitching and
complaining about Lee.

422
00:28:13.443 --> 00:28:14.754
And that damn Baldwin memorial

423
00:28:14.778 --> 00:28:17.215
that's been up for a month
is not helping matters.

424
00:28:17.239 --> 00:28:20.868
Tear it down. It is a violation of base law.

425
00:28:21.493 --> 00:28:25.747
I can't tear it down. they'll only build
another and they will hate me even more.

426
00:28:26.331 --> 00:28:29.877
I must unite the people. not
make it worse than it already is.

427
00:28:35.382 --> 00:28:37.843
Remember the launch parties

428
00:28:38.510 --> 00:28:42.931
they used to throw in star city?

429
00:28:44.099 --> 00:28:45.809
How could I forget?

430
00:28:47.102 --> 00:28:49.897
We met at one of these parties.

431
00:28:51.857 --> 00:28:53.609
Every man there wanted you.

432
00:28:54.860 --> 00:28:58.405
But you were the only salmon
to make it to the top of the falls.

433
00:29:06.830 --> 00:29:07.873
Lenya.

434
00:29:08.665 --> 00:29:10.143
Please.

435
00:29:10.167 --> 00:29:11.168
Think.

436
00:29:12.294 --> 00:29:14.254
Why do we celebrate these launches?

437
00:29:15.047 --> 00:29:17.233
The Americans do it too.

438
00:29:17.257 --> 00:29:21.595
So does helios. Esa. Even
the north Koreans. Why?

439
00:29:23.388 --> 00:29:26.016
A shared sense of purpose.

440
00:29:27.100 --> 00:29:29.204
I would wager ferdinand and Isabella

441
00:29:29.228 --> 00:29:33.273
threw a hell of a party for Columbus
before he sailed across the Atlantic.

442
00:29:41.740 --> 00:29:43.283
The titan mission.

443
00:29:44.576 --> 00:29:46.078
Precisely.

444
00:29:46.662 --> 00:29:48.539
Something for the people to rally behind.

445
00:29:49.581 --> 00:29:53.561
And it doesn't hurt that ed
Baldwin's daughter is on the crew.

446
00:29:53.585 --> 00:29:56.588
Honey. What would I do without you?

447
00:30:04.513 --> 00:30:06.014
How far away is this?

448
00:30:07.224 --> 00:30:08.350
Just another minute.

449
00:30:12.938 --> 00:30:14.189
Jesus Christ.

450
00:30:15.065 --> 00:30:16.233
How's everything going?

451
00:30:16.859 --> 00:30:18.944
Yeah. Yeah. everybody's been really nice.

452
00:30:21.238 --> 00:30:23.883
I'm actually back down another
floor. But you're good. yeah?

453
00:30:23.907 --> 00:30:26.678
Yeah. I'm good. Hey.
thanks for being my guide.

454
00:30:26.702 --> 00:30:27.786
Yeah. of course.

455
00:30:29.037 --> 00:30:31.140
Ms. Rosales. he's expecting you.

456
00:30:31.164 --> 00:30:34.727
- Can I get you a coffee or something?
- I'm okay.

457
00:30:34.751 --> 00:30:36.587
Ms. Rosales? Right this way.

458
00:30:37.754 --> 00:30:39.214
Did you want some coffee?

459
00:31:03.030 --> 00:31:04.031
Wow.

460
00:31:29.223 --> 00:31:31.903
I thought I'd give you a moment
to savor what we've built together.

461
00:31:34.269 --> 00:31:35.354
Dev.

462
00:31:39.274 --> 00:31:41.068
I need to talk to you about…

463
00:31:42.152 --> 00:31:43.695
I am so glad you're finally here.

464
00:31:45.739 --> 00:31:48.158
I'm so glad you finally came
up. I've been waiting for you.

465
00:31:51.787 --> 00:31:53.056
Okay.

466
00:31:53.080 --> 00:31:55.415
But the fact remains

467
00:31:55.999 --> 00:32:00.271
that this company has
become dysfunctional. Dev.

468
00:32:00.295 --> 00:32:02.023
We can't keep working
at cross purposes.

469
00:32:02.047 --> 00:32:03.817
I'm trying to keep helios solvent.

470
00:32:03.841 --> 00:32:08.154
meanwhile you're spending hand
over fist on this fucking city on Mars.

471
00:32:08.178 --> 00:32:10.240
Which you announced without
even giving me a heads-up.

472
00:32:10.264 --> 00:32:11.449
Hey. look. I get it.

473
00:32:11.473 --> 00:32:13.559
I haven't always been the
most communicative person.

474
00:32:14.852 --> 00:32:17.062
But in my life. I've lost trust in people.

475
00:32:18.272 --> 00:32:20.333
Been stabbed in the back
by those closest to me.

476
00:32:20.357 --> 00:32:22.677
See. the difference with
me is I'll stab you in the front.

477
00:32:23.277 --> 00:32:24.570
I don't doubt that.

478
00:32:25.571 --> 00:32:28.407
So are we good? Or are we
gonna talk about our feelings all day?

479
00:32:35.163 --> 00:32:36.498
All right.

480
00:32:37.165 --> 00:32:38.792
Then let's get down to business.

481
00:32:39.710 --> 00:32:40.770
Two things.

482
00:32:40.794 --> 00:32:44.524
First is that the new plasma engines
on sojourner aren't reaching rated power.

483
00:32:44.548 --> 00:32:46.234
Won't even get us to orbit.

484
00:32:46.258 --> 00:32:48.093
Second. if we do get them to work.

485
00:32:48.677 --> 00:32:51.197
we're gonna hit titan's
atmosphere like a bat out of hell.

486
00:32:51.221 --> 00:32:54.117
We need more accurate
atmospheric scale-height calculations

487
00:32:54.141 --> 00:32:55.493
for the aerobraking maneuver.

488
00:32:55.517 --> 00:32:57.912
Don't we have the data
from Walt's seekers?

489
00:32:57.936 --> 00:32:58.997
Yes.

490
00:32:59.021 --> 00:33:01.064
But that won't match
conditions when we get there.

491
00:33:01.565 --> 00:33:03.209
Without real time scale-height figures…

492
00:33:03.233 --> 00:33:06.087
Sojourner might just skip off the
atmosphere and get sucked into saturn.

493
00:33:06.111 --> 00:33:08.631
Or come in too hot. Burn up on entry.

494
00:33:08.655 --> 00:33:10.073
So bad day either way.

495
00:33:12.993 --> 00:33:15.388
Kuragin's planning an aerobrake
maneuver for their mission.

496
00:33:15.412 --> 00:33:17.432
They must have a scale-height
figure for those conditions.

497
00:33:17.456 --> 00:33:20.059
- They'd be crazy to launch without it.
- So how'd they get theirs?

498
00:33:20.083 --> 00:33:23.086
Pretty sure they'd consider
that proprietary information.

499
00:33:25.714 --> 00:33:26.757
Okay.

500
00:33:27.299 --> 00:33:28.675
I think I have a solution.

501
00:33:29.593 --> 00:33:30.753
But I'm gonna need some time.

502
00:33:33.430 --> 00:33:34.890
If we don't get that number.

503
00:33:36.141 --> 00:33:37.202
they'll beat us.

504
00:33:37.226 --> 00:33:38.393
I'll get it.

505
00:33:54.034 --> 00:33:55.094
- Good morning.
- Morning.

506
00:33:55.118 --> 00:33:56.745
- What's up. Mario?
- What's up?

507
00:33:57.871 --> 00:34:00.183
G money. which server has
the space elevator schematics?

508
00:34:00.207 --> 00:34:04.020
I just need to know how much weight
the platform can hold for the meru cargo.

509
00:34:04.044 --> 00:34:07.714
Server 36. axl Rose.

510
00:34:09.174 --> 00:34:11.236
Why are all your
references from the '80s?

511
00:34:11.260 --> 00:34:13.387
Takes longer for shit to get to ussr.

512
00:34:27.650 --> 00:34:30.338
Are you… I'm sorry.
are you sure this is it?

513
00:34:30.362 --> 00:34:31.780
Yes. cowboy.

514
00:34:32.697 --> 00:34:36.845
I ever see a man holding
a bull by the tail. you're it.

515
00:34:36.869 --> 00:34:38.471
My god. Please stop.

516
00:34:38.495 --> 00:34:39.955
Rio bravo.

517
00:34:55.262 --> 00:34:57.490
- Sorry. Ms. Joshi.
- Yes?

518
00:34:57.514 --> 00:35:01.119
I just can't seem to get access
to this folder on server 36.

519
00:35:01.143 --> 00:35:02.144
Yeah.

520
00:35:03.812 --> 00:35:05.415
You have to have level
three security clearance

521
00:35:05.439 --> 00:35:07.000
from the m-6 for files with that heading.

522
00:35:07.024 --> 00:35:08.543
And how do I get that?

523
00:35:08.567 --> 00:35:10.587
Took six months from when I applied.

524
00:35:10.611 --> 00:35:12.279
Can I just use your computer then?

525
00:35:13.322 --> 00:35:14.323
Nice try.

526
00:35:22.247 --> 00:35:24.601
It was. like. weird. You know?

527
00:35:24.625 --> 00:35:26.978
The folder was in cyrillic.
which I only kind of understand

528
00:35:27.002 --> 00:35:30.440
because my grandma kept. like.
drilling it into my head as a kid. but…

529
00:35:30.464 --> 00:35:31.465
It said…

530
00:35:35.886 --> 00:35:36.970
Automation.

531
00:35:38.972 --> 00:35:40.015
Why is that weird?

532
00:35:40.557 --> 00:35:42.869
'Cause the space elevator isn't
supposed to use any automation.

533
00:35:42.893 --> 00:35:45.229
The unions made.
like. a big fuss about it.

534
00:35:48.315 --> 00:35:49.995
Well. what do you think is in that folder?

535
00:35:51.068 --> 00:35:52.069
Wow. Are…

536
00:35:52.569 --> 00:35:55.507
Sorry. are you asking me right
now. or are you reporting for nnc?

537
00:35:55.531 --> 00:35:56.949
- Is that… yeah.
- Shut up.

538
00:35:57.699 --> 00:36:00.369
Like they actually ask me to do
anything besides make coffee.

539
00:36:02.246 --> 00:36:04.039
Seriously. what do you think's in it?

540
00:36:07.501 --> 00:36:09.187
I don't know. okay?

541
00:36:09.211 --> 00:36:11.773
I couldn't see it. I didn't have
the proper clearance level.

542
00:36:11.797 --> 00:36:13.191
Come on.

543
00:36:13.215 --> 00:36:14.455
When has that ever stopped you?

544
00:36:15.634 --> 00:36:18.071
Remember when you hacked
into the vending machines on sl2

545
00:36:18.095 --> 00:36:20.824
and we had free soda
for. like. all of junior year?

546
00:36:20.848 --> 00:36:23.475
Yeah. and I almost got suspended for it.

547
00:36:25.477 --> 00:36:26.770
You almost.

548
00:37:27.831 --> 00:37:29.333
When I was growing up.

549
00:37:30.250 --> 00:37:31.668
he was just a picture on a wall.

550
00:37:33.879 --> 00:37:35.714
My mother told me
how much he loved me.

551
00:37:36.715 --> 00:37:38.634
and when I was little. I believed that.

552
00:37:40.552 --> 00:37:42.221
I used to lie in bed at night…

553
00:37:44.306 --> 00:37:47.309
look out the window at the stars…

554
00:37:49.853 --> 00:37:52.314
Thinking maybe
somebody made a mistake

555
00:37:54.066 --> 00:37:55.817
and that he was still alive up there.

556
00:38:00.739 --> 00:38:03.700
That one day he would just land
his spaceship in the backyard.

557
00:38:06.286 --> 00:38:09.873
Scoop me up in his arms and
tell me how much he missed me.

558
00:38:12.709 --> 00:38:14.628
When did you learn the truth about him?

559
00:38:15.379 --> 00:38:16.588
High school.

560
00:38:17.798 --> 00:38:20.092
The other kids started
calling me "psycho bitch."

561
00:38:21.218 --> 00:38:23.053
Said I was as crazy as my old man.

562
00:38:25.389 --> 00:38:28.559
I'd take it for as long as I
could. then I'd start fighting back.

563
00:38:33.146 --> 00:38:34.690
Is that why you joined the corps?

564
00:38:35.357 --> 00:38:36.650
To prove them wrong?

565
00:38:38.068 --> 00:38:39.111
No.

566
00:38:43.657 --> 00:38:45.409
I joined to serve my country.

567
00:38:47.661 --> 00:38:49.788
Same as my dad and his dad before him.

568
00:39:10.559 --> 00:39:13.413
Ma'am. the lidar density maps
and atmospheric thermal profiles

569
00:39:13.437 --> 00:39:16.082
you requested from
Dr. Griebel finally arrived.

570
00:39:16.106 --> 00:39:19.586
Also. I printed out that monthly
operations report that you asked for.

571
00:39:19.610 --> 00:39:20.694
Good. Thank you.

572
00:39:21.236 --> 00:39:23.071
Also. knocking first would be nice.

573
00:39:24.740 --> 00:39:27.218
Sorry. we actually have
an open door policy here.

574
00:39:27.242 --> 00:39:29.220
Dev doesn't really
believe in closed doors.

575
00:39:29.244 --> 00:39:31.205
Well. I do.

576
00:39:32.581 --> 00:39:33.790
Yes. ma'am.

577
00:39:35.209 --> 00:39:36.710
Wait. Hold on. come back.

578
00:39:38.545 --> 00:39:40.607
It says here that a
delegation from kuragin

579
00:39:40.631 --> 00:39:42.692
is slated to come up here next week?

580
00:39:42.716 --> 00:39:45.153
Does it have anything to
do with our titan launch?

581
00:39:45.177 --> 00:39:48.072
I'm sure it has something to do
with the space elevator construction.

582
00:39:48.096 --> 00:39:49.389
It is behind schedule.

583
00:39:50.849 --> 00:39:53.077
Get me whatever
information you can on them.

584
00:39:53.101 --> 00:39:54.228
Yes. ma'am.

585
00:41:04.173 --> 00:41:05.174
Okay.

586
00:41:17.311 --> 00:41:18.437
Joshi priya.

587
00:41:28.739 --> 00:41:30.532
Okay. Here we go.

588
00:41:53.597 --> 00:41:54.741
Okay.

589
00:41:54.765 --> 00:41:58.727
"Replacement of Mars
personnel with automation."

590
00:41:59.353 --> 00:42:04.149
"Achieve automation of
98% of all Mars operations"?

591
00:42:05.609 --> 00:42:06.610
What the hell?

592
00:42:15.202 --> 00:42:16.203
Fuck it. Fuck it.

593
00:42:39.351 --> 00:42:41.353
Look at you burning the midnight oil.

594
00:42:43.313 --> 00:42:45.625
Sorry. I didn't mean to
scare you. I know it's late.

595
00:42:45.649 --> 00:42:47.252
It's totally all right.

596
00:42:47.276 --> 00:42:50.654
I'm sorry. I just… I get
so focused. you know?

597
00:42:51.822 --> 00:42:52.865
I like your desk.

598
00:42:53.907 --> 00:42:55.826
Yes. yeah. Thank you.

599
00:42:56.869 --> 00:42:58.203
So what are you working on?

600
00:43:02.457 --> 00:43:03.876
Just data entry.

601
00:43:04.501 --> 00:43:06.378
Mainly… you know?

602
00:43:09.756 --> 00:43:12.176
Hey. don't put too much
pressure on yourself. okay?

603
00:43:13.218 --> 00:43:15.530
Not the worst thing to take a
break every once in a while.

604
00:43:15.554 --> 00:43:17.198
Yes. Yeah. yeah.

605
00:43:17.222 --> 00:43:19.892
Feel that. Feel that. A lot.

606
00:43:24.605 --> 00:43:26.249
Starting right… I will
take a break right now.

607
00:43:26.273 --> 00:43:28.418
- You take a break right now.
- Yes. Yeah.

608
00:43:28.442 --> 00:43:30.522
- See you later. kiddo.
- Have a good night. aleida.

609
00:43:34.406 --> 00:43:35.824
Holy shit.

610
00:43:54.218 --> 00:43:55.445
Jesus Christ.

611
00:43:55.469 --> 00:43:56.696
Yeah.

612
00:43:56.720 --> 00:43:59.073
It's not just about the space elevator.

613
00:43:59.097 --> 00:44:00.408
- They're gonna…
- automate everything.

614
00:44:00.432 --> 00:44:03.953
Asteroid mining. iridium refinery. the
metal mills. the hopper. even Phoenix.

615
00:44:03.977 --> 00:44:05.038
They can't do this.

616
00:44:05.062 --> 00:44:06.456
They already are doing it.

617
00:44:06.480 --> 00:44:08.917
Kuragin's been bringing equipment
up here for months. off the books.

618
00:44:08.941 --> 00:44:10.835
And then what happens
to everybody living here?

619
00:44:10.859 --> 00:44:12.337
- Their jobs are...
- it says here

620
00:44:12.361 --> 00:44:14.961
that they'll just ship everyone
back to earth within a few years.

621
00:44:17.074 --> 00:44:18.825
We gotta let people know about this.

622
00:44:19.868 --> 00:44:22.663
I can give it to my boss at nnc. and I…

623
00:44:23.413 --> 00:44:24.665
What?

624
00:44:25.666 --> 00:44:28.710
- What? What is it? Alex…
- yeah. I just…

625
00:44:31.463 --> 00:44:33.131
I just… I need to talk to Dev.

626
00:44:34.091 --> 00:44:37.946
- Alex.
- No... he's clearly involved in this.

627
00:44:37.970 --> 00:44:39.989
But it doesn't make sense. He
believes in Mars more than anybody.

628
00:44:40.013 --> 00:44:42.850
Then why were these files
found on helios servers?

629
00:44:43.433 --> 00:44:46.311
Everybody knows that nothing
happens over there without his say so.

630
00:44:50.357 --> 00:44:53.920
Look. I know you're close with him. but
we have to let people know about this.

631
00:44:53.944 --> 00:44:55.737
I need some time to think about it. okay?

632
00:45:01.118 --> 00:45:02.119
Okay.

633
00:45:11.420 --> 00:45:12.629
Coke. please.

634
00:45:27.519 --> 00:45:29.205
That shit before.

635
00:45:29.229 --> 00:45:30.230
We were drunk.

636
00:45:31.690 --> 00:45:33.108
Sorry things got out of hand.

637
00:45:34.151 --> 00:45:35.485
Anyway. fuck the poly. right?

638
00:45:36.153 --> 00:45:37.797
You're a good marine.

639
00:45:37.821 --> 00:45:39.990
Those machine don't know shit. anyway.

640
00:45:41.658 --> 00:45:42.659
Well…

641
00:45:44.745 --> 00:45:47.247
Then I guess it's too bad that I passed.

642
00:45:48.081 --> 00:45:49.082
You what?

643
00:45:49.750 --> 00:45:50.751
You heard me.

644
00:45:54.671 --> 00:45:56.149
Yo!

645
00:45:56.173 --> 00:45:57.549
Tabasco's going to the moon!

646
00:46:01.261 --> 00:46:08.995
Tabasco! Tabasco!
Tabasco! Tabasco! Tabasco!

647
00:46:09.019 --> 00:46:11.289
Tabasco! Tabasco!

648
00:46:11.313 --> 00:46:12.707
Good job.

649
00:46:12.731 --> 00:46:15.734
Tabasco! Tabasco! Tabasco!

650
00:46:17.236 --> 00:46:18.320
See you later.

651
00:46:35.879 --> 00:46:37.649
Ladies and gentlemen.

652
00:46:37.673 --> 00:46:42.445
I am very proud to introduce
you to these intrepid adventurers.

653
00:46:42.469 --> 00:46:47.992
Now. they're about to expand
mankind's reach by one billion kilometers

654
00:46:48.016 --> 00:46:49.768
as they journey to titan.

655
00:46:50.894 --> 00:46:52.229
The moon of saturn.

656
00:46:52.813 --> 00:46:55.875
And their aim is to bring back

657
00:46:55.899 --> 00:47:00.320
what possibly is the first
life from another world.

658
00:47:10.956 --> 00:47:14.459
They include flight
engineer Stuart Fraser.

659
00:47:17.379 --> 00:47:19.298
Geologist Elena beaufort.

660
00:47:21.049 --> 00:47:24.595
Flight engineer and propulsion
specialist. Oleg vyshinsky.

661
00:47:25.721 --> 00:47:28.158
Mission pilot. Kelly Baldwin.

662
00:47:28.182 --> 00:47:30.350
And commander Walt griebel.

663
00:47:31.393 --> 00:47:32.704
Settle down.

664
00:47:32.728 --> 00:47:34.229
Settle down. please.

665
00:47:34.813 --> 00:47:39.276
It is easy for us sometimes
to forget why we're all here.

666
00:47:40.027 --> 00:47:41.862
But we are all explorers.

667
00:47:42.446 --> 00:47:46.384
It is because each and every
single one of you that this…

668
00:47:46.408 --> 00:47:48.368
This endeavor doesn't fall apart.

669
00:47:49.870 --> 00:47:51.931
So today is a celebration.

670
00:47:51.955 --> 00:47:53.290
But not only of the mission.

671
00:47:53.999 --> 00:47:57.002
It's a celebration of you.
who make it possible.

672
00:47:58.253 --> 00:48:03.383
Now this is a proof of what we can
achieve when we all come together.

673
00:48:04.134 --> 00:48:09.598
Each one of you helping to push
mankind's reach further into the stars.

674
00:48:16.563 --> 00:48:17.689
Alex?

675
00:48:18.857 --> 00:48:20.025
In here.

676
00:48:23.862 --> 00:48:25.113
Hey.

677
00:48:26.323 --> 00:48:27.366
Hey.

678
00:48:29.034 --> 00:48:30.118
You okay?

679
00:48:31.787 --> 00:48:32.829
Yeah. Course.

680
00:48:35.541 --> 00:48:36.893
You sure?

681
00:48:36.917 --> 00:48:40.563
Yes. yes. I'm fine. Stop worrying.

682
00:48:40.587 --> 00:48:41.922
So…

683
00:48:43.632 --> 00:48:45.008
last night on Mars?

684
00:48:47.386 --> 00:48:48.595
I know.

685
00:48:49.721 --> 00:48:51.849
And I picked up just
the thing to celebrate.

686
00:48:53.517 --> 00:48:55.245
What. spaghetti night?

687
00:48:55.269 --> 00:48:57.413
Come on. I need your
help with the garlic bread.

688
00:48:57.437 --> 00:48:58.832
Okay. I'll be right there.

689
00:48:58.856 --> 00:49:00.190
- All right.
- Okay.

690
00:49:25.549 --> 00:49:27.443
Engine self-check is nominal. flight.

691
00:49:27.467 --> 00:49:29.821
Ascent. is sojourner go
to initiate start sequence

692
00:49:29.845 --> 00:49:31.698
on ascent engines one through six?

693
00:49:31.722 --> 00:49:36.685
Pumps armed. magnetic containment active.
rf power on standby. Go for engine start.

694
00:49:54.494 --> 00:49:55.680
Ma'am.

695
00:49:55.704 --> 00:49:57.307
I have that information you asked for.

696
00:49:57.331 --> 00:49:58.415
Thank you.

697
00:50:25.317 --> 00:50:26.318
Aleida.

698
00:50:27.486 --> 00:50:28.487
Aleida.

699
00:50:29.905 --> 00:50:31.156
Ready for launch.

700
00:50:36.954 --> 00:50:38.306
Let's get started then.

701
00:50:38.330 --> 00:50:40.666
Capcom. tell sojourner
we have a green board.

702
00:50:41.625 --> 00:50:45.629
Sojourner-titan. we show all
systems go for your ascent.

703
00:50:46.964 --> 00:50:49.049
Copy. Mars. We're as
ready as we'll ever be.

704
00:50:50.717 --> 00:50:51.885
Vasimr status?

705
00:50:52.511 --> 00:50:54.888
Reactors nominal. tokamaks stable.

706
00:50:56.098 --> 00:50:57.742
Ich is powering up.

707
00:50:57.766 --> 00:51:00.495
Injectors now at operating pressure.

708
00:51:00.519 --> 00:51:04.731
Ascent engines show green.
main stage engines at standby.

709
00:51:05.566 --> 00:51:07.860
Guidance is now running
program four zero two.

710
00:51:08.569 --> 00:51:10.362
L-minus six.

711
00:51:10.863 --> 00:51:14.241
Five. Four. Three.

712
00:51:15.242 --> 00:51:18.912
Two. One. Zero.

713
00:51:22.583 --> 00:51:24.001
We have lift-off.

714
00:51:25.794 --> 00:51:28.172
And clear. Twenty meters

715
00:51:29.423 --> 00:51:30.549
100 meters.

716
00:51:31.758 --> 00:51:33.218
Good ascent profile.

717
00:51:33.802 --> 00:51:36.763
Secure a rotate to
azimuth zero-niner-seven.

718
00:51:38.307 --> 00:51:41.226
Rotating to azimuth zero-niner-seven.

719
00:51:42.603 --> 00:51:44.271
Mainstage thrusters ready.

720
00:51:47.441 --> 00:51:50.068
And forward motion.

721
00:51:56.992 --> 00:51:58.511
From the reports we're receiving.

722
00:51:58.535 --> 00:52:02.432
today marked a successful launch
for sojourner-t and her crew of five.

723
00:52:02.456 --> 00:52:04.958
- a mission funded by helios aerospace.
- To my husband

724
00:52:05.626 --> 00:52:08.587
who successfully reunited
the people of happy valley.

725
00:52:09.421 --> 00:52:11.089
I'm proud of you.

726
00:52:11.757 --> 00:52:13.151
Thank you. little rabbit.

727
00:52:13.175 --> 00:52:15.594
…endeavoring to land
on titan. a moon of saturn.

728
00:52:16.762 --> 00:52:20.182
Their objective is nothing
less than to discover life.

729
00:52:20.724 --> 00:52:22.785
The crew includes exobiologist…

730
00:52:22.809 --> 00:52:24.913
Are you having trouble
focusing. my dear husband?

731
00:52:24.937 --> 00:52:26.915
…daughter of renowned
astronaut Edward Baldwin…

732
00:52:26.939 --> 00:52:27.999
Maybe I can help with that.

733
00:52:28.023 --> 00:52:29.417
…who recently passed away.

734
00:52:29.441 --> 00:52:32.504
She joins a team lead by Walt griebel.

735
00:52:32.528 --> 00:52:36.174
The implications of such a
discovery would be groundbreaking.

736
00:52:36.198 --> 00:52:40.011
potentially reshaping how
humanity conceives of itself…

737
00:52:40.035 --> 00:52:42.597
- I'm turning it off.
- …potential applications

738
00:52:42.621 --> 00:52:45.308
for bio medicine here on earth.

739
00:52:45.332 --> 00:52:48.061
The pharmaceutical
corporations are taking note.

740
00:52:48.085 --> 00:52:51.296
positioning themselves to
cut deals with either helios…

741
00:52:52.089 --> 00:52:53.691
What is it?

742
00:52:53.715 --> 00:52:55.342
…this discovery.

743
00:53:29.042 --> 00:53:30.210
What is it?

744
00:53:52.858 --> 00:53:55.461
Not surprisingly. helios
and kuragin's stock

745
00:53:55.485 --> 00:53:56.737
have both plummeted…

746
00:54:14.254 --> 00:54:15.255
My god.
